					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Charles IX of France"/>
					<location name="France"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>Charles IX, king of France.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="90">
					<marginalia_text>
						&Ocirc; qu&agrave;m magnificum, vbiq[ue] esse audacem, et inuictum?
						Qui sapit, ad multa animum non applicabit: sed pauca priuatim, aut public&egrave;
						vtilissima perficiet, quanta potest facultate maxima.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>O how magnificent is it, that there is boldness and invincibility everywere? <!--JG: Unsure-->
			He who understands, will not apply the mind to many things, but to a few things in private or publicly, he will
			accomplish the most useful things, as much as he can with the greatest ability.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="180">
					<marginalia_text>
						Qui timescit, Vilescit. Qui tristescit,
						<!-- Continues onto facing page, tail, Ha2.205v -->
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>He who is frigthened, becomes worthless. He who becomes sad,</translation> <!--JG: Unsure about 'tristescit'-->
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						Quantum ulla fieri potest vel arte, vel philosophia, vel professione
						maximum: vel omnin&ograve; aliquoa humana facultate.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						Ca[e]tera minuta, aut vulgaria linquenda
						ociosis, aut rerum ignaris.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>As much as can be done either with any art, philosophy, or profession: or entirely with another human faculty. <!--JG: Unsure-->
			The remaining faculties having been diminished, or the common ones must be left with those idle or ignorant of matters.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
